Class MWRevision

  org.apache.uima.wikipedia.types.MWRevision
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<MWRevision>
public class MWRevision
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<MWRevision>

This class represents an article's revision. It is designed to be immutable, thus allowing fluent access to it's data fields without fearing user's modifications.

Revisions are crafted by the revision factory. Some of the tags we consider in our analysis are optional, the corresponding field will be initialized with a default value if the tag is not present. We also only consider the contributor's username. For more details on this see MWRevisionFactory.

Revisions can be ordered according to their timestamp. Newer revisions are considered greater than older ones.

Constructs a new MWRevision object. Once initialized, the fields can't be modified anymore, thus making this object immutable.

Parameters:
id - The revision's id.
timestamp - The revision's timestamp
contributor - The name of the revision's contributor
minor - A flag indicating if revision is minor or not
comment - The optional comment of the contributor on this revision
text - The text of the revision
